http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Japan-offers-aid-for-waste-management/article14006731.ece

A Japanese delegation has offered to assist Kochi to set up an anaerobic waste management system in the city. The visiting delegation held discussions with the civic authorities here on Monday.Japan has offered to convert the organic waste collected at Brahmapuram into “high quality compost rapidly utilising aerobic fermentation technologies with almost no leachate and odour.” They have also offered funding opportunities for the project, said a communication issued by Deputy Mayor T.J. Vinod.A presentation on the project would be made at the Council, he said. The civic heads including the chairpersons of the Standing Committees attended the meeting.